headline: ZBH Stock Gains From FDA Nod for Oxford Cementless Partial Knee
summary: Zimmer Biomet receives FDA nod for the Oxford Cementless Partial Knee. It is a PMA Supplement approval. The company plans a nationwide launch in the first quarter of 2025.

headline: Zimmer wins FDA approval for cementless partial knee implant
summary: The device is established in Europe, where the company said it has a 60% market share, but will be the first product of its type available in the U.S.
